@70001  = ~mystic~
@70002  = ~Mystic~
@70003  = ~MYSTICS: Through study and meditation, Mystics form a spiritual connection with some aspect of the natural world, and channel energy through that connection to create magical effects. This art has been practiced in some fashion since the dawn of time, before there were religions or deities; some say Mystics are the original magic-users. 

PURE MYSTICS form a deep, spiritual connection with a fundamental aspect of the universe: one of the prime elements, or light or shadow. The magic that flows through them is raw and powerful, but their ability to shape it is limited to effects closely related to their focus.

DRUIDS are a branch of Mystics focused on the balanced combinations of elemental energies that result in living ecosystems. At the direction of the deities Sylvanus and Chauntea, they have organized themselves into ordered hierarchies in which to teach and practice their abilities. They have mastery over various facets of the natural world: different chapters specialize in particular environments, such as forests, jungles, mountains, and deserts.

OCCULTISTS learn to tap magical power in nontraditional ways. Through study and unnatural experiments, they can learn to harness the boiling energies of the inner planes, or infernal powers from the outer planes, or the wild, animal nature seething inside every man and woman. Some have even learned to steal magical energy from the deities themselves - calling into question whether those beings are truly omnipotent.

All of these classes share some common attributes. Creating and maintaining the spiritual connections to perform this type of magic is very demanding. Therefore, they may not spare the time to master the use of complicated or martial weapons; they are excluded from using 2-handed swords, halberds, katanas, bastard swords, long swords, flails, morning stars, maces, and crossbows. 
~
