@70101  = ~nature mystic~
@70102  = ~Nature Mystic~
@70103  = ~NATURE MYSTIC: The Nature Mystic taps the inherent energies of life that exists wherever there are thriving ecosystems of plants and animals. Once, these were the most common kind of mystic in human communities. Now, practitioners of this magic are very rare now, having been supplanted by the ordered ranks of Druids under the supervision of Sylvanus. Most Druids now consider Nature Mystics to be heretics, practicing a dangerous and less refined version of their art. Druids nevertheless respect the source of these Mystics' power, and in the rare case they cross paths, grudgingly allow Mystics to participate in their magic rituals.

Advantages:
- May cast one extra spell per level
- Casts spells as if one level of experience higher
- Immune to poison and disease
- May cast a short, single-target Entanglement spell at will. This keeps the target from moving for one round and, on a failed save vs. Breath, Holds the target still and causes 1d4 points of piercing damage.
- 15% of all melee hits Entangle the target as described above
- May allocate 2 points (++) to Single-Weapon Style and Two-Handed Style, and 3 points (+++) to Two-Weapon Style.

Restrictions:
- Must be Neutral
~
